  "statement": {
    "markdown": "## Game Overview\nCreate a Memory Card Game with the following features:\n### Requirements\n1. The game should display a grid of 16 memory cards with unique values (numbers from 1 to 8).\n2. Each memory card should have a front and back side. The front side displays the card value, while the back side is blank.\n3. When a card is clicked, it should flip to its back side. After a short delay (at least 1000ms), it should flip back to its front side.\n4. Two cards can only be flipped at the same time if they have different values. If they have the same value, only the first one should flip.\n5. The game should keep track of the number of pairs found and display it at the top of the game grid.\n6. The game should have a 'play again' button that restarts the game with new card values."
  },
  "constraints": [
    "Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling.",
    "JavaScript and HTML/CSS are the only allowed technologies.",
    "Use JavaScript's setTimeout() function for the card flip delay.",
    "Implement a 'game over' condition when all pairs are found, and display a message with the game result."
  ],
